entries.title: Brits told not to mail anything abroad after cyber incident
entries.description: A cyber incident has prompted the U.K.’s Royal Mail to ask the nation’s 67 million citizens not to send anything overseas for the time being.

entries.title: Intel’s Core i9-13900KS hits 6GHz out of the box, but there’s a catch
entries.description: Intel's latest CPU, the Core i9-13900KS, has just arrived. This monstrous chip is pushing the limits in more ways than one.
